d gone though all my supplies and my skill had risen to 36. All of the medium jars I made, I threw them away for I did not want to spend the money on firing sheets. <br><br>I was no longer gaining training for the jars, so I purchased around 150 Medium Bowl Sketches, 150 Blocks of clay and 150 flasks of water. I quickly made many bowls and threw them away for I did not want to spend the money on firing sheets. Within 1 hour of starting the whole task, I had become a master of pottery with spend 25 platinum on supplies. <br><br>I find this very funny for I was only planning on learning the basics, not mastering it in an hour. If anyone needs help doing the same, feel free to speak with me about it.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.graphicomm.com/~spikep/brut.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ubrutredblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutredblade</A> at: 2/13/02 5:09:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jeffryn>Jeffryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#330000>(2/13/02 8:54:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1404.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to do with 1 hour and 25 platinum - A story of Trai</span><hr size=1> Hehe....I think it funny you went to the moon because it was closest!  I mean, think about that for a moment...  <br><br>(Zoning and game mechanics aside.)  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.